[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(8) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "At this house, which is high.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The word “which” is not in the original Hebrew here (although found in the present Hebrew text of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 7:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The true meaning is certainly “This house shall be high;” which is the reading of the LXX., while the Vulg. has a good explanatory gloss, “This house shall be for an example.” Various corrections have been proposed, but there seems no necessity for them. There is evidently an allusion to the lofty position of the Temple. Generally the exaltation of “the mountain of the Lord” is made a type of its glory (as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Micah 4:1-2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 68:15-16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", &c.); here of its destruction. Its magnificence and its ruin are equally conspicuous: for “a city set on a hill cannot be hid.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Kings 9:8-9. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 9:8-9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And at this house, which is high — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Exalted in its privileges, and renowned for its riches and splendour, and the great resort of people to it. They gloried in the stateliness and magnificence of the structure; but God here lets them know it was not so high as to be out of the reach of his judgments, which should assuredly fall upon it and them, if they vilified it so as to exchange it for groves and idol-temples, and yet, at the same time, most inconsistently and absurdly magnified it, so as to suppose it would secure the favour of God to them, although they ever so much corrupted themselves. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Every one that passeth by it shall be astonished — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "At its unexpected and wonderful ruin. As they who now pass by it are astonished at the bulk and beauty, the richness, contrivance, and workmanship of it, and call it a stupendous fabric; so, if you forsake God, its height will make its fall the more amazing, and they that pass by will be as much astonished at its ruins. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And shall hiss — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "By way of contempt and derision; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and shall say, Why hath the Lord, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — What is the reason that this famous place, which boasted so much of the favour and protection of God, is thus laid in ruins? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And they shall answer, Because they forsook, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — The guilty, self-convicted, self-condemned Israelites will be forced to acknowledge with shame, that they themselves were the ruin of it. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 29:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Their sin will be read in their punishment. They deserted the temple, and therefore God deserted it; they profaned it with their sins, and laid it common; and therefore God profaned it with his judgments, and laid it waste. Of this God thus gave Solomon fair warning, now he had newly built and dedicated it, that he and his people might not be ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "high-minded, but fear.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "9:1-9 God warned Solomon, now he had newly built and dedicated the temple, that he and his people might not be high-minded, but fear. After all the services we can perform, we stand upon the same terms with the Lord as before. Nothing can purchase for us liberty to sin, nor would the true believer desire such a licence. He would rather be chastened of the Lord, than be allowed to go on with ease and prosperity in sin.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Hebrew text runs - \"And this house shall be high: every one,\" etc. The meaning appears to be, \"This house shall be high\" (i. e., conspicuous) \"in its ruin as in its glory.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And shall hiss - In contempt. This expression first appears in the time of Hezekiah 2 Chronicles 29:8; Micah 6:16. It is especially familiar to Jeremiah (Jeremiah 18:16; Jeremiah 19:8, etc.). ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "And shall hiss - In contempt. This expression first appears in the time of Hezekiah ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 29:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Micah 6:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". It is especially familiar to Jeremiah (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 18:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 19:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", etc.). ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
