  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "this house",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " which ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "is high",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The connexion of these words is very difficult. The Hebrew text, standing alone, must be rendered ‘And this house shall be high.’ But in 2 Chron. the relative is expressed, and there can be little doubt that the text here is somehow faulty. The passage in 2 Chron. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 7:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") reads ‘And this house which is high shall be an astonishment.’ To come as near to this sense as possible, while introducing no relative, R.V. gives ‘",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "And though this house be high",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".’ Yet that rendering is somewhat doubtful. The text of the LXX. shows that they had our Hebrew before them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καὶ ὁ οἶκος οὖτος ἔσται ὁ ὑψηλός",
        "children": []
